BEGIN_PGML

 A cylindrical pressure vessel with hemispherical endcaps, diameter [`D`] and wall thickness [`T`], contains gas at pressure [`p`]. The elastic properties of the wall material are [`E`] and [`v`]. 
1. Derive a formula for the change in diameter of the pressure vessel at a point away from the ends. 
2. Repeat part the first part for a spherical pressure vessel of diameter [`D`] and wall thickness [`t`]. 
3. A cylindrical pressure vessel as described in part (1) has hemispherical end caps as described in part (2) Determine the ratio of the wall thicknesses [`\frac{t}{T}`] that will eliminate St. Venant type distortions near the ends.  

_Hint: The end distortions occur if the change in diameter of the end caps is different from that of the cylinder_.

[`\Delta D_c=`] [________________]{"$ddc"}  
[`\Delta D_s=`] [________________]{"$dds"}  
[`\frac{t}{T}=`] [________________]{"$tt"}  

